Subject:     ISG EXECUTIVE BOARD DECISIONS ON STRATEGIC TASK FORCE 
             RECOMMENDATIONS


We are happy to announce our decisions regarding three of the four 
vertical industry markets under study by Strategic Task Forces.  
The attached set of Administrative Bulletins details those 
decisions.  Next month we will hear recommendations from our 
Communications Industry Task Force, and will decide on a long-term 
strategy for the McDonnell Douglas Communications Industry Systems 
Company.

We are convinced the course we have chosen is consistent with the 
ISG Vision, and with our objective of operating the ISG as a 
dynamic partnership of vertical and horizontal/resource 
businesses.  We are announcing these decisions well ahead of our 
1 July deadline, and are hopeful that we can have the new 
businesses operating by that date.

Along with these new vertical business decisions, the Executive 
Board has made two additional decisions that affect existing ISG 
organizations:

     1)  In order to more appropriately describe the mission of 
         the organization recently formed by combining 
         McDonnell Douglas Network Systems Company with the 
         North American Sales force of the McDonnell Douglas 
         Computer Systems Company, this combined organization has 
         been renamed the McDonnell Douglas Business and Network 
         Systems Company.  Warren Prince will continue to head 
         this organization under the new title of 
         President - McDonnell Douglas Business and Network 
         Systems Company.  As before, Warren will report to the 
         ISG Executive Board through Gary Liebl.

     2)  In order to bring the name and status of the Commercial 
         Processing Centers (CPC) organization into line with the 
         other ISG companies, this organization has been 
         designated the McDonnell Douglas Information Processing 
         Company.  Ted Bellan will continue to head this 
         organization under the new title of President - McDonnell 
         Douglas Information Processing Company.  As before, Ted 
         will report to the ISG Executive Board through Bob 
         Fischer.






By midyear the ISG's basic structure will be complete.  That 
structure will consist of the following businesses:


Industry-Dedicated Vertical Businesses
______________________________________

     McDonnell Douglas Health Systems Company

     McDonnell Douglas Manufacturing and Engineering Systems 
     Company

     McDonnell Douglas Financial Transaction Systems Company

     McDonnell Douglas Distribution Systems Company

     McDonnell Douglas Communications Industry Systems Company


Multi-Industry Horizontal/Resource Businesses
_____________________________________________

     McDonnell Douglas Diversified Information Systems Company

     McDonnell Douglas Business and Network Systems Company

     McDonnell Douglas Computer Systems Company

     McDonnell Douglas Field Service Company

     McDonnell Douglas Information Processing Company


International Distributor
_________________________

     McDonnell Douglas Information Systems International Company


Restructuring the ISG has demanded much of our attention over the 
past year.  Now, with that structure virtually complete, we can all 
focus our attention on what really counts from here on out -- 
serving our customers and attaining our revenue and earnings 
objectives.



