Subject:      FORMATION OF MCDONNELL DOUGLAS FINANCIAL TRANSACTION 
              SYSTEMS COMPANY

After carefully considering the recommendations of the Strategic 
Task Force on Financial Services, the ISG Executive Board has 
decided to form the McDonnell Douglas Financial Transaction 
Systems Company.

The company's mission will be to build a major vertical industry 
business based on electronic point-of-sale services to retailers, 
financial institutions and service establishments.

The McDonnell Douglas Financial Transaction Systems Company will 
have an objective of generating 1990 revenues of $0.5 billion, and 
after-tax profits of $40 million (in 1983 dollars).

The company's strategy for achieving those goals is:

    1)   To more aggressively market our TeleCheck check 
         acceptance service across a broad range of retail 
         establishments.

    2)   To introduce a proprietary system to electronically 
         authorize checks and market that system to high-volume 
         retail establishments.

    3)   To market computer and communications services to credit 
         and debit card companies.

    4)   To pursue opportunities in the area of Automated Clearing 
         House (ACH) services.

In addition, the company will continue to evaluate several 
proposed strategies, including electronic bill payment, credit 
reporting and Automated Teller Machine (ATM) services.

The McDonnell Douglas Financial Transaction Systems Company will 
include the current McDonnell Douglas Payment Systems Company.  
The two other business units within the ISG's Financial Services 
Organization - McDonnell Douglas Banking Systems Company and 
McDonnell Douglas International Banking and Investment Systems 
Company - will transfer to McDonnell Douglas Diversified 
Information Systems Company.  This move will make the sales 
organization of the McDonnell Douglas Diversified Information 
Systems Company available to these companies and will concentrate 
in one place the industry-dedicated products the ISG sells to 
banks





The McDonnell Douglas Financial Transaction Systems Company will 
report to the ISG Executive Board through Bob Fischer.  It is 
planned that the President of the McDonnell Douglas Financial 
Transaction Systems Company will be recruited externally.  Until 
this position is filled, Alden Heintz, who is appointed President 
- McDonnell Douglas Payment Systems Company, will report to 
Bob Fischer, who will serve as acting President of the McDonnell 
Douglas Financial Transaction Systems Company.

John Mazzola, former Project Director of the Financial Services 
Strategic Task Force, along with Jeff Baer and David Jung, members 
of that Task Force, will form a team to develop a business plan 
and a plan to fill out the new company's organizational 
structure.  McDonnell Douglas Financial Transactions System 
Company is expected to be in operation effective 1 July 1985.

