Subject:     FORMATION OF MCDONNELL DOUGLAS DISTRIBUTION SYSTEMS 
             COMPANY


After carefully considering the recommendations of the Strategic 
Task Force on Wholesale/Retail Distribution, the ISG Executive 
Board has decided to form the McDonnell Douglas Distribution 
Systems Company.

The company's mission will be to establish a strong ISG presence in 
the retail industry by providing information solutions to a full 
range of businesses involved in all phases of distribution, from 
manufacturers and suppliers through brokers and wholesalers to 
retail stores and chains.

McDonnell Douglas Distribution Systems Company will have an 
objective of generating 1990 revenues of $0.4 billion and after-tax 
profits of $30 million (in 1983 dollars).

The company's strategy for reaching those goals will be:

    1)   To provide distribution management systems.

    2)   To provide integrated in-store systems such as inventory 
         control and automated ordering systems linked to laser 
         scanners and electronic cash registers.

    3)   To provide electronic data interchange (EDI) systems that 
         interconnect a full range of businesses involved in 
         distribution.

    4)   To provide electronic marketing services that allow 
         retailers to focus their marketing efforts by means of 
         in-store systems that display product information to 
         customers.

The company will focus initially on the supermarket industry.  
Additional lines of trade to be developed later include chain 
drugstores, discount stores and "do-it-yourself" home supply 
centers.  Eventually, the company will address such soft goods and 
fashion merchandise markets as department stores and specialty 
stores.

The McDonnell Douglas Distribution Systems Company, headquartered 
in the southern California area, will combine the current 





McDonnell Douglas Distribution Information Systems Company and the 
McDonnell Douglas Electronic Data Interchange Company.  The new 
company will include some of the distribution industry capabilities 
currently in the McDonnell Douglas Computer Systems Company.

The new company will be headed by Otis Brinkley, who is promoted to 
President - McDonnell Douglas Distribution Systems Company.  He 
will report to the ISG Executive Board through Gary Liebl.  Further 
appointments will be announced later.

A team has been formed to develop a business plan and a plan to 
fill out the company's organizational structure.  The company is 
