Diversified Information Systems Company.  The following changes 
take effect 1 July 1985:

  1)  Rich Calvert is promoted to Senior Vice President and 
      General Manager - McDonnell Douglas Diversified Information 
      Systems Company.  Rich replaces Otis Brinkley, who is 
      promoted to President of the newly formed McDonnell Douglas 
      Distribution Systems Company.

  2)  The McDonnell Douglas Architectural, Engineering and 
      Construction Information Systems Company is transferred to 
      the McDonnell Douglas Manufacturing and Engineering Systems 
      Company.  This change will align compatible CAD offerings 
      under one vertical industry company.

