Subject:  PROPERTY CONTRIBUTIONS TO NON-PROFIT INSTITUTIONS


Personal  property  items  and  equipment may be contributed to a
non-profit  institution.    This is primarily applicable to items
that  have  been  determined  to  be  surplus  to MDC needs.  MDC
Policy  #4,  and  ISG  Management Directive #101, as contained in
the   ISG   Management   Handbook,   indicates  specific  advance
coordination/approvals to authorize such contributions:

    o  All   contributions   of   property  having  and  original
       acquisition  cost  of  $1000  or  less  per  item  require
       approval  of  the  applicable  ISG Company Head (Component
       Head).

